This +130 page novel study is for teaching Cam Jansen #1: The Mystery of the Stolen Diamonds in English to Mandarin-speaking Chinese children. It is divided into eight sections, one for each chapter of the book, and includes everything you'll need to teach the book in a systematic way. Click the green preview button and try the first chapter for FREE.

Inside each section you'll find:

- comprehension questions about the story with space for students to answer in full sentences;

- a writing prompt where students can express their opinions about topics related to the text;

- a vocabulary list with Mandarin translations of key words to save on dictionary time and reduce confusion;

- a word search puzzle for students to enjoy some quiet time to familiarize themselves with the vocabulary;

- a sequencing worksheet to identify the order important events happen in the story; and

- a chapter quiz to assess the students' comprehension.

This product also includes these end-of-book activities:

- a final test;

- a comic strip project;

- an illustrator worksheet;

- a crossword puzzle;

- a chapter summarizer;

- a prediction worksheet;

- a book cover project; and

- a book report assignment.

